How would you fix it for lambdas? I commonly see this pattern:

```
post([this]() {
   this->some_ref->something()
 });
```

This will generate a segfault if the callback is executed after the destruction of `this`. If the callback has a shared_ptr to this (shared_from_this()) or captures shared ptrs to `some_ref`, then this becomes much safer.
